","text":"A dedicated look-and-feel is implemented for that if the "},{"code":"isError","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" flag is risen."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","text":"Accessibility considerations","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note also the component must be instanciated with a string parameter used as accessibility label."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It is a good pratice (at least) to define a label for a component without text for accessibility reasons. This label will be vocalized by "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Voice Over","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The vocalization tool will also use, after the label, a description of the component (if disabled, if error context), and a fake trait for checkbox."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Cases-forbidden-by-design","text":"Cases forbidden by design","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a disabled component."}],"type":"strong"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Code-samples","text":"Code samples","level":2},{"code":["    \/\/ Supposing we have a selected checkbox","    @Published var isOn: Bool = true","","    \/\/ A simple checkbox, no error, not in read only mode","    OUDSCheckbox(isOn: $isOn, accessibilityLabel: \"The cake is a lie\")","","    \/\/ A simple checkbox, but is an error context","    OUDSCheckbox(isOn: $isOn, accessibilityLabel: \"The cake is a lie\"), isError: true)","","    \/\/ Never disable an error-related checkbox as it will crash","    \/\/ This is forbidden by design!","    OUDSCheckbox(isOn: $isOn, accessibilityLabel: \"The cake is a lie\"), isError: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Design-documentation","text":"Des